            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Agree, I didn't realize I can that. Thank you.\n\nOne thing that I noticed is that generated C code doesn't mark if statement itself with unlikely:\n```\nif (unlikely(val == 42)) {\n```\ninstead, it marks a temporary var, something like this\n```\n  __pyx_t_2 = unlikely(__pyx_t_1);\n  if (__pyx_t_2) {\n```\n\nI checked in the compiler explorer if it makes any difference, and it does for clang! Clang completely ignores unlikely on a variable.\n\nBut it works for gcc!.\n\nhttps://godbolt.org/z/x8PKKszT8\n\nSince I'm using gcc, it works for me 😃 \n\nMy problem is solved, and I'm happy to close this, but do you think it is something that you would be interested in making more reliable?\n\n\n",
